      <hedline>
        <hl1>Taking a Closer Look At the Peril of Plum Island</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rev Judy Fine letter on August 13 article on Plum Island tests of 'mad' sheep suggests Long Island facility be shut down (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Re: ''Plum I. May Test 'Mad' Sheep'' [Aug. 13].</p>
        <p>Welcome to the first public abusement park. Come and see the fascinating sight of a cow being clinically poisoned with ''mad cow'' disease. And for the sake of variety, watch a sheep go through the horrific stages of the disease.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Re: ''Plum I. May Test 'Mad' Sheep'' [Aug. 13].</p>
        <p>Welcome to the first public abusement park. Come and see the fascinating sight of a cow being clinically poisoned with ''mad cow'' disease. And for the sake of variety, watch a sheep go through the horrific stages of the disease.</p>
        <p>This and more at Plum Island Abusement Park.</p>
        <p>And for the individual who doesn't really care about animal suffering, let me invite you to take a look at the possibility that a mosquito will carry the deadly virus back to Long Island after having a blood meal on a dying sheep or cow. Think about it! We're all at risk.</p>
        <p>What to do? Shut down Plum Island.</p>
        <p>(The Rev.) JUDY FINE  Healdsburg, Calif.</p>
      </block>
